				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Tanking With Your Hands in your Pockets<a name="24389"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 28 04 6:51 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>On Karana server late at night when I do most of my adving, there's almost never a decent tank available, so having successfully tanked a few as an experiment, I now find I tank the majority of the hard advs.  Made a discovery a couple of nights ago ... something the wars and pallies have known all along.  Don't melee.  My clerics were burning through a lot of mana keeping me up, and emeralds for that matter, until I just stopped hitting the attack key.  Over HALF the damage the hard mobs do is in riposts, so if you're the MT, twist 3 DoTs (4 if your system can keep up with that) slow and keep one hand on your drum and the other firmly in your pocket.
<br />

<br />
Dlandridel Cadence
<br />
Maestro of Grey Hawke
<br />
Karana Server  </span></td>
